Additional_Comments: Downstream of the stop riders have to basically walk in the road to get to the stop because of a fence that is right next to the curb. Upstream of the stop, riders have etched a path in the grass where a sidewalk should be. The paved boarding area is narrow and close to the fast moving traffic on the road. The trash can is not on the boarding area making it difficult to access for those with disabilities. There is also no safe way to cross to the other side of the street without dodging 5 lanes of traffic. This stop is not safe, accessible, or dignified!
